    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, add your <strong>cod fillet[s]</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Lay a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over each piece of cod, sprinkle over your <strong>dried oregano</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 12 min or until the cod is cooked through – this is your <strong>herby cod</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
